WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.000
And give her a teaspoon of the medicine after every meal.

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
Don't worry, she'll be fine.

00:15.000 --> 00:17.000
You're welcome.

00:17.000 --> 00:18.000
Goodbye.

00:18.000 --> 00:30.000
How are you?

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
I'm tired and hungry.

00:32.000 --> 00:34.000
Well, Marilyn and Richard called.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
They'll be here soon and then we'll eat.

00:36.000 --> 00:37.000
All right.

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
Is Susan coming?

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
She'll be here later.

00:41.000 --> 00:42.000
She has to work late tonight.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.000
And what's Robbie cooking for dinner?

00:44.000 --> 00:47.000
It's a surprise.

00:47.000 --> 00:50.000
I hope it's pasta.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.000
Robbie, the dinner was terrific.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
Yes, it was delicious.

00:55.000 --> 00:57.000
What's for dessert?

00:57.000 --> 01:00.000
Hot dessert.

01:00.000 --> 01:04.000
Don't worry.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
We've got lots of ice cream.

01:06.000 --> 01:08.000
Oh, I'd love some ice cream.

01:08.000 --> 01:11.000
Well, there's chocolate and chocolate.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.000
I have vanilla.

01:12.000 --> 01:14.000
Is that all right with everyone?

01:14.000 --> 01:15.000
I'll have chocolate.

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
Me too.

01:17.000 --> 01:22.000
One scoop of coffee and one scoop of chocolate for me.

01:22.000 --> 01:25.000
Robbie, will you help me, sir?

01:25.000 --> 01:28.000
Mm.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
Mm.

01:30.000 --> 01:44.000
I keep thinking about that bag of film.

01:44.000 --> 01:49.000
Eight rolls, a whole day's work, and good stuff too.

01:49.000 --> 01:51.000
Don't worry, Richard.

01:51.000 --> 01:53.000
Someone will find it.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.000
Mm.

01:54.000 --> 01:57.000
I'll get it.

01:57.000 --> 01:58.000
All right.

01:58.000 --> 02:03.000
Hello.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.000
Hello.

02:05.000 --> 02:08.000
Does Richard Stewart live here?

02:08.000 --> 02:10.000
Yes, he's my brother.

02:10.000 --> 02:11.000
I'm Robbie.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.000
Robbie Stewart.

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
I'm Alexandra Papas.

02:14.000 --> 02:16.000
How do you do?

02:16.000 --> 02:19.000
Your brother left his bag of film on the ferry boat.

02:19.000 --> 02:20.000
I found it.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
I'm really glad to see you.

02:22.000 --> 02:26.000
I mean, my brother will be really glad to see you.

02:26.000 --> 02:29.000
Robbie, who is it?

02:29.000 --> 02:31.000
It's Richard's film.

02:31.000 --> 02:34.000
I mean, Alexander Papas.

02:34.000 --> 02:39.000
Come in, please.

02:39.000 --> 02:42.000
Alexandra.

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
Hello, Richard.

02:44.000 --> 02:45.000
I found your bag.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.000
Oh, thank you.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
Thank you.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Alexandra, let me introduce you.

02:51.000 --> 02:52.000
This is my wife, Marilyn.

02:52.000 --> 02:54.000
Richard showed me your photo.

02:54.000 --> 02:55.000
How do you do?

02:55.000 --> 02:56.000
Oh, yes.

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
Richard told us all about you.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.000
It's nice to meet you.

02:59.000 --> 03:01.000
And this is my mother, Ellen Stewart.

03:01.000 --> 03:02.000
How do you do?

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
And my father, Dr. Philip Stewart.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
Nice to meet you, Alexandra.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.000
And you met Robbie.

03:07.000 --> 03:08.000
Yes.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
And you must be Susan.

03:10.000 --> 03:11.000
Hi.

03:11.000 --> 03:12.000
Hi.

03:12.000 --> 03:13.000
Welcome.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
I'm so glad you found the bag and took the time and trouble to return it.

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
Oh, it was no trouble.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
I just took the wrong train.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
Would you like something to eat?

03:22.000 --> 03:23.000
Thank you.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.000
No.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
I'm late for dinner at my house.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.000
I really have to go.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
Would you like to call home?

03:29.000 --> 03:30.000
I'd appreciate that.

03:30.000 --> 03:31.000
Please.

03:31.000 --> 03:32.000
Use the phone.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.000
Thanks.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.000
Excuse me.

03:34.000 --> 03:37.000
Alexandra's a high school exchange student from Greece.

03:37.000 --> 03:38.000
Where did she live?

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
With a family in the Bronx.

03:40.000 --> 03:42.000
Oh, that's not too far from here.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
Take it easy, Robbie.

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
Thank you.

03:46.000 --> 03:50.000
I can only stay a few minutes.

03:50.000 --> 03:51.000
Have Iced tea.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
Thanks, Mrs. Stewart.

03:53.000 --> 03:55.000
Please sit down, Alexandra.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.000
So you're an exchange student.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
Where do you go to school?

04:06.000 --> 04:08.000
At the Bronx High School of Science.

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
Oh, that's a very good school.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
What are your favorite subjects?

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
Biology and mathematics.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
Richard tells me you're a doctor.

04:17.000 --> 04:19.000
Yes, a pediatrician.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.000
And what does your father do?

04:21.000 --> 04:24.000
He's a lawyer in Thessaloniki.

04:24.000 --> 04:25.000
Would you like some pasta?

04:25.000 --> 04:26.000
I made it myself.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.000
It might be a little cold.

04:29.000 --> 04:30.000
Thanks.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.000
No.

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
I do have to go.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
It was nice meeting you all.

04:35.000 --> 04:37.000
Well, maybe he'll come for lunch some Sunday

04:37.000 --> 04:40.000
so we can really thank you for bringing Richard's bag back.

04:40.000 --> 04:41.000
Maybe.

04:41.000 --> 04:43.000
You're welcome anytime.

04:43.000 --> 04:44.000
Goodbye.

04:44.000 --> 04:51.000
Can I drive you home?

04:51.000 --> 04:52.000
No, thanks.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.000
The train is just up the street.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.000
It won't take me long at all.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
You really saved the day for me, Alexandra.

04:57.000 --> 04:58.000
Bye.

04:58.000 --> 04:59.000
Bye.

04:59.000 --> 05:00.000
Bye.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.000
Good night.

05:01.000 --> 05:03.000
She's a smart young lady.

05:03.000 --> 05:04.000
And very nice.

05:04.000 --> 05:05.000
Very.

05:05.000 --> 05:08.000
Hey, she forgot her bag.

05:08.000 --> 05:11.000
Oh, I guess we'll be seeing Alexandra again.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
Right, Robbie.

05:13.000 --> 05:15.000
She's very...

05:15.000 --> 05:17.000
Hey, she forgot her bag.

05:17.000 --> 05:20.000
I guess we'll be seeing Alexandra again.

05:20.000 --> 05:21.000
Right, Robbie?

